    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="856"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12704.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                        General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your course in urging delegates to continue their journey to Saltillo is most
                    cordially approved. Any seeming discourtesy shown by Constitutionalists must
                    have been due to oversight rather than intention. We are very anxious for the
                    conference to take place and see no reason for its failure. Keep us fully
                    informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
